# allObjects

**Instance Property**

The array of unenumerated objects.

## Declaration

```swift
var allObjects: [Any] { get }
```

## Discussion

This array contains all the remaining objects of the enumerator in enumerated order. It does not contain objects that have already been enumerated with previous [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSEnumerator/nextObject()] messages.

Accessing this property exhausts the enumerator’s collection so that subsequent invocations of [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSEnumerator/nextObject()] return `nil`.

## Related Documentation

- **Collections Programming Topics**

## Getting the Enumerated Objects

- **nextObject()**: Returns the next object from the collection being enumerated.
